Q: A student can't remember the formula for the area of a triangle, so he uses the formula for the area of a parallelogram. What is the area of the parallelogram if the base and height are 5 and 8 meters respectively? [asy]

draw((0,0)--(5,0)--(5,8)--cycle);
draw((0,0)--(5,8));
label("5",(2.5,0));
label("8",(5,4));
[/asy]

A: The area of the parallelogram is 40 square meters.
